	Harmison set to retire after Ashes   
	London: Injury-ravaged England pacer Steve Harmison is all set to retire from international cricket after the ongoing Ashes series. According to a report in a British daily, Harmison will follow his best friend Andrew Flintoff by announcing his retirement from Test cricket after the Ashes. The 30-year-old, who retired from one-day cricket in 2007, is reportedly tired of the numerous injury-breakdowns.  
